etymologies: Middle English: from gray (variant of gray) + -ling

definitions: an edible freshwater fish of Eurasia and North America that is silvery-gray with horizontal violet stripes and has a long, high dorsal fin.

notes.text: Genus Thymallus, family Salmonidae: several species

shortDefinitions: edible freshwater fish which is silvery-grey with horizontal violet stripes

definitions: a mainly brown European butterfly which has wings with bright eyespots and grayish undersides.

notes.text: Hipparchia semele, subfamily Satyrinae, family Nymphalidae

shortDefinitions: mainly brown European butterfly which has wings with bright eyespots
